Y.P. Rai has joined as the new Chief Post Master General, Andhra Pradesh Postal Circle covering AP and Telangana on Monday.He did his doctorate in Biochemistry from Jawaharlal Nehru University, New Delhi. He is also a graduate from Defence Services Staff College, Wellington. He joined Indian Postal Service in 1984. Besides, holding various appointments in the Department of Posts, he also served in Army and Central government in various capacities.Prior to joining as Chief Postmaster General, Andhra Pradesh Postal Circle, he worked as Chief Postmaster General, Chhattisgarh Postal Circle.- Special Correspondent